()System Property kya hai?
System Property ek key-value pair hoti hai jo system ya application ke liye configuration settings store karti hai.
Key: Property ka naam (jaise defaultPassword)
Value: Property ka actual value (jaise Welcome@123)
Ye properties program me kahin bhi access ho sakti hain, jaise workflow, rules, ya provisioning me.

()Java / SailPoint me example:-

1️⃣ Check property exist karti hai ya nahi:-
boolean exists = context.isProperty("defaultPassword");
System.out.println("Property exists? " + exists);

Output:-
Property exists? true

2️⃣ Property ka value lena:-
String value = context.getProperty("defaultPassword");
System.out.println("Property value: " + value);

Output:-
Property value: Welcome@123

1️⃣ System ka matlab:-
Ye ek computer ya application environment hota hai jahan program run hota hai.
Isme include hota hai:-
Server: Jahan application host hoti hai (jaise web server, SailPoint server).
Operating System: Windows, Linux, etc.
Application/Software: Jaise SailPoint IdentityNow ya IdentityIQ.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Common SailPoint System Properties List (koi na chute):-
#	Property Name	                                                            Description
1	sailpoint.application.defaultPassword---------------------------Default password for new accounts
2	sailpoint.application.defaultEmail------------------------------Default email address for new accounts
3	sailpoint.application.accountNamePattern---------------------------Naming pattern for new accounts
4	sailpoint.provisioning.reconciliationEnabled---------------------Enable/disable reconciliation process
5	sailpoint.provisioning.defaultManager---------------------------Default manager for provisioning requests
6	sailpoint.audit.logLevel----------------------------------------Audit log level (INFO, DEBUG, ERROR)
7	sailpoint.audit.logFile--------------------------------------------Path of audit log file
8	sailpoint.scheduler.jobThreadPoolSize-------------------------------Thread pool size for scheduler jobs
9	sailpoint.workflow.defaultLocale----------------------------------Default locale/language for workflows
10	sailpoint.identity.validation.enabled----------------------------Enable/disable identity validation
11	sailpoint.system.notification.emailServer--------------------------SMTP server for system notifications
12	sailpoint.system.notification.fromAddress-----------------------------Default “from” email address
13	sailpoint.ui.sessionTimeoutMinutes------------------------------------UI session timeout in minutes
14	sailpoint.ui.maxLoginAttempts----------------------------------------Max login attempts before lockout
15	sailpoint.policy.violation.notifyOwner---------------------------------Notify owner on policy violation
16	sailpoint.policy.violation.autoMitigate---------------------------------Auto-mitigation enabled/disabled
17	sailpoint.rule.defaultExecutionContext--------------------------------Default execution context for rules
18	sailpoint.connector.retryCount--------------------------------------------Number of retries for connector failures
19	sailpoint.connector.timeoutSeconds----------------------------------------Timeout for connector calls in seconds
20	sailpoint.logging.debugEnabled------------------------------------------Enable/disable debug logging
21	sailpoint.logging.traceEnabled------------------------------------------Enable/disable trace logging
22	sailpoint.environment-----------------------------------------------Environment name (DEV, QA, PROD)
23	sailpoint.version--------------------------------------------------------SailPoint system version
24	sailpoint.custom.property.-------------------------------------------*Any custom property defined by admin
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()Server kya hai?

Server ek aisa computer ya program hai jo data ya services provide karta hai doosre computers ya users ko, jo usse request bhejte hain.

Matlab: Server serve karta hai, client request karta hai.

1️⃣ SailPoint / Enterprise System Servers:-
SailPoint environment me usually ye servers hoti hain:-
#	Server Type	                                                  Description
1	Application Server:------------------------------Jahan SailPoint application deploy hoti hai (Tomcat, JBoss, WebLogic)
2	Database Server:---------------------------------Backend database (Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL) jahan identity data store hota hai
3	Email Server / SMTP Server:-----------------------Notifications aur alerts ke liye
4	Scheduler Server:--------------------------------Background jobs aur workflow executions ke liye
5	Web Server / Proxy Server:-----------------------User requests route karne ke liye (Apache, Nginx)
6	Connector Server / Target Systems:-----------External systems jisse identity info sync hoti hai (Active Directory, SAP, Salesforce)
7	Audit / Logging Server:-------------------------Logs aur audit trails store karne ke liye
8	Authentication / SSO Server:---------------------Single Sign-On aur authentication ke liye (AD FS, Okta)
9	Dev / QA / Test Servers:-------------------------Development aur testing environment ke liye

2️⃣ General Common Servers Types (Any IT Environment):-
File Server – Files store aur share karne ke liye
Database Server – Structured data store karne ke liye
Web Server – Websites serve karne ke liye
Application Server – Business logic run karne ke liye
Mail Server – Emails send/receive ke liye
Proxy Server – Requests route karne aur security ke liye
DNS Server – Domain name ko IP me convert karne ke liye
FTP Server – File transfer ke liye
Game Server – Multiplayer games host karne ke liye
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
